  "response_text": "A brief opening image shows three yellow Milk-Bone dog biscuit boxes standing in grass, with dogs pictured on the packages and large white text along the bottom reading “Better Teeth Cleaner.” The commercial then shifts to a bright domestic gathering in a living room or dining area. An older, silver-haired man in a dark suit, white shirt, and striped tie stands at a counter beside a cream-colored Mr. Coffee drip coffee maker. He holds a small white cup near his mouth. The coffee maker has a squared, boxy top with a dark front panel and control strip, and a black glass carafe filled with dark coffee sits underneath.\n\nA smiling woman with shoulder-length dark hair, wearing a light patterned blouse and pale high-waisted pants, approaches him holding a yellow rectangular check or rebate slip. She faces him warmly as he lowers his cup. They stand close beside the coffee maker, with other guests seated at small tables in the background. The room has light curtains, houseplants, and a soft, sunny 1970s living-room atmosphere. The woman leans in and kisses the man on the cheek, then smiles and begins to walk away, still holding the yellow paper.\n\nThe man remains at the counter with the Mr. Coffee machine prominently to his right. He turns toward the viewer, holding his white cup in one hand. On the counter in front of him lies another yellow check. He gestures toward the appliance, then picks up the check and brings it forward. As he holds it closer, the check fills much of the view. It is pale yellow and printed with “MR. COFFEE” at the upper left, a portrait of the silver-haired man on the left side, and a boxed “$5.00” amount on the right. A large cursive signature across the lower portion reads “Joe DiMaggio,” matching the audio context that identifies the signature.\n\nHe lowers the check back toward the counter and continues standing beside the machine, one hand near the cup and the other near the appliance. Behind him, several adults sit and move around small tables, suggesting a social coffee gathering or card-club setting. A woman in a light outfit works near a window, while others converse in the background.\n\nThe scene then focuses on one of the guests: a middle-aged woman with short, curled light-brown hair. She wears a light blue blouse with darker blue vertical accents or suspenders. She lifts a white cup to her lips, drinks, and then lowers it slightly with a pleased smile. Other hands and cups appear around her; one person holds a cup on a saucer at her left. She looks upward and to the side, smiling as if reacting to someone nearby.\n\nMore of the table group becomes visible. A woman in a tan or rust-colored blouse stands beside the seated woman, holding a white cup and saucer. The older silver-haired man is now seated at the left edge, also holding a white cup. In the foreground on the table is a clear glass Mr. Coffee carafe filled with dark coffee, resting on a low white warming base. The seated woman in blue keeps smiling with her cup raised. The standing woman reaches toward the carafe, grasps it by the handle, and lifts it from the base while the others continue holding their cups.\n\nThe final display shifts to a staged product lineup against a warm yellow background. The silver-haired man stands at the left in his dark suit, beside several Mr. Coffee appliances arranged across a counter. Three upright automatic drip coffee makers are shown, each with a black glass carafe beneath a squared cream or white body, and a low carafe-and-warmer unit sits among them. Yellow rebate checks are displayed in front of the products. Large white lettering across the top reads, “The MR. COFFEE $5.00 Rebate.” Smaller white text along the bottom reads, “See stores for details. Offer ends Nov/30/1978.”",
